  1. Add a glTF loader layer

  - Use tinygltf to parse .gltf/.glb.
  - Extract: nodes, meshes, primitives, accessors, bufferViews, materials, textures.

  2. Change geometry path from “single procedural mesh” to “many primitives”

  - glTF mesh = multiple primitives.
  - Each primitive has its own vertex/index ranges + material.
  - Your draw loop becomes for node -> for primitive -> vkCmdDrawIndexed(...).

  3. Expand vertex format

  - At minimum for glTF:
      - POSITION (required)
      - NORMAL (optional but usually needed)
      - TEXCOORD_0 (for baseColorTexture)
      - COLOR_0 (optional, but common)
  - Keep missing attributes with defaults in shader/CPU.

  4. Add index buffer support (required in practice)

  - Most glTF primitives are indexed.
  - Support index component types: UNSIGNED_SHORT and UNSIGNED_INT (and ideally
    UNSIGNED_BYTE).

  5. Add node transform handling

  - glTF is hierarchical.
  - Compute world matrix from parent*local and pass per-draw (push constants or SSBO index).

  6. Add minimal material system

  - Support pbrMetallicRoughness.baseColorFactor.
  - Support baseColorTexture (sRGB sampled image).
  - Bind per-material descriptors (or material buffer + texture array later).

  7. Update shaders

  - New vertex shader: position/normal/uv/color + MVP/world.
  - New fragment shader: baseColorFactor * texture(baseColorTexture) * vertexColor.
  - Keep simple directional+ambient lighting for now.

  8. Pipelines

  - Start with one pipeline (opaque).
  - Then add variants as needed:
      - alpha blend (alphaMode=BLEND)
      - alpha mask (alphaMode=MASK with discard)
      - double-sided (cull off)

  9. Passes

  - Single render pass is enough for minimal glTF.
  - Multiple passes are only needed later for advanced PBR/IBL/shadows/post.

  So for your direct questions:

  - “Just vertex/index upload?” -> Not enough; also scene graph + materials + textures + per-
    primitive draw logic.
  - “Set number of pipelines?” -> 1 initially, then 2-4 variants for alpha/cull correctness.
  - “Multiple shaders?” -> At least one glTF-aware VS+FS pair; more only for variants.
  - “Multiple passes?” -> No, one pass is fine for minimal support.

  If you want, next I can give you a concrete integration skeleton (GltfModel, GltfPrimitive,
  GltfMaterial, and exact command buffer pseudocode) mapped to your current
  State::buildPipeline style.
